ANSI pumps, also known as ANSI standard pumps, refer to a specific type of centrifugal pump that conforms to the standards set by the American National Standards Institute (ANSI). The ANSI standard for pumps, specifically ASME B73.1, provides guidelines for the design, construction, and performance of centrifugal pumps used in industrial applications.

