The term "ANSI pump" typically refers to a centrifugal pump that adheres to the dimensional and operational standards specified by the ANSI B73.1 standard. These pumps are commonly used in industries such as chemical processing, oil and gas, power generation, water treatment, and more.



The ANSI standard ensures interchangeability and compatibility between different pump manufacturers. It establishes standard dimensions for mounting, shaft, impeller, and casing sizes, as well as standardizing performance parameters such as flow rate, head pressure, and temperature limits.



The purpose of adhering to ANSI standards is to provide a consistent and reliable framework for pump selection, installation, and maintenance. ANSI pumps are known for their durability, efficiency, and ease of maintenance due to the standardized design and interchangeability of components.



